    "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rdk/p2rank/zipball/2.6-alpha",
    "body": "Feature release: new pocket-level outputs, more flexible structure handling (non-canonical residues, cofactors), and wider rescoring support. Some features are included as preview for early feedback.\r\n\r\n### Main changes\r\n\r\n- **External conservation provider** - conservation-aware models (`conservation_hmm`, `alphafold_conservation_hmm`) can now run locally by fetching scores on demand from a conservation HTTP server; previously only usable through [PrankWeb](https://prankweb.cz). Includes local on-disk cache and server health check. &nbsp; \u2192 **[conservation docs](https://github.com/rdk/p2rank/blob/develop/documentation/conservation.md)**\r\n- **Extended non-canonical residue mapping** (Issue #79) - modified amino acid residues commonly found in PDB structures (selenomethionine, phosphoserine, D-amino acids, ...) can be mapped to their canonical counterparts so they contribute to AA-type-dependent features (propensity tables, residue-type one-hot, etc.) instead of being treated as unknown. Bundled table derived from [pdbfixer](https://github.com/openmm/pdbfixer); custom CSV mappings also supported. Enable with `-aa_mapping pdbfixer` (opt-in; default unchanged). &nbsp; \u2192 **[AA mapping docs](https://github.com/rdk/p2rank/blob/develop/documentation/aa-mapping.md)**\r\n- Added **rescoring** support for more third-party pocket predictors: **SwinSite**, **Seq2Pocket**, **Pocketeer**. &nbsp; \u2192 **[rescoring docs](https://github.com/rdk/p2rank/blob/develop/documentation/rescoring.md)**\r\n- New `pocket` rank column in the SAS points export (Issue #82), enabling per-pocket aggregation of SAS features. &nbsp; \u2192 **[export-points docs](https://github.com/rdk/p2rank/blob/develop/documentation/export-points.md)**\r\n- Performance: rewritten 3D KdTree for faster neighbor queries, fewer hot-path allocations, updated FasterForest (faster inference, optional vector-API / native acceleration).\r\n- Requires Java 17+ (tested up to Java 26).\r\n\r\n\r\n### Preview features\r\n\r\nAnything user-visible (behaviour, parameters, defaults, output formats) may shift through the **2.6** cycle, and some features may stay in preview into a later release. Feedback welcome.\r\n\r\n- **Cofactor-as-protein-surface** mode (Issue #79) - common cofactors (`FAD`, `PLP`, `HEM`, ...) can be treated as part of the protein surface rather than as ligands. More biologically realistic predictions on structures where a cofactor occupies part of the binding site, and avoids the cofactor being labeled as the predicted pocket. &nbsp; \u2192 **[cofactors docs](https://github.com/rdk/p2rank/blob/develop/documentation/cofactors.md)**\r\n  - enable with `-cofactors 'FAD,PLP,HEM,...'` (explicit HETATM codes; also per-structure via a `cofactors` column in the dataset file)\r\n\r\n- **Pocket descriptors** - one row per predicted pocket with scalar geometric properties: **volume**, sphericity, radius of gyration, principal moments. Configurable set. &nbsp; \u2192 **[pocket descriptors docs](https://github.com/rdk/p2rank/blob/develop/documentation/export-pocket-descriptors.md)**\r\n  - `-export_pocket_descriptors 1` - emit as `CSV` / `Arrow` / `Parquet`.\r\n\r\n- **Pocket grid** - 3D point cloud sampling the empty space of each pocket, with optional per-grid-point descriptors (e.g. VolSite-style pharmacophore indicators). Useful for pocket similarity, pharmacophore search, or voxel-based ML. &nbsp; \u2192 **[pocket grid docs](https://github.com/rdk/p2rank/blob/develop/documentation/export-pocket-grid.md)**\r\n  - `-export_pocket_grid 1` - emit as `CSV` / `Arrow` / `Parquet`.\r\n  - `-vis_pocket_grid 1` - PyMOL `.pml` + ChimeraX `.cxc` overlays (volumetric surfaces and grid points).\r\n\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n\r\nSame default prediction models as version **2.4**.\r\n\r\n\r\nExisting users: see the [list of breaking changes](https://github.com/rdk/p2rank/blob/develop/breaking-changes.md).\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\">\r\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/rdk/p2rank/blob/develop/documentation/img/visualization/pocket_grid_chimerax.png?raw=true\">\r\n    <img src=\"https://github.com/rdk/p2rank/blob/develop/documentation/img/visualization/pocket_grid_chimerax_small.png?raw=true\" height=230\" alt=\"ChimeraX visualization of pockets as volumes / grid points\"></a>\r\n  \r\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/rdk/p2rank/blob/develop/documentation/img/visualization/pocket_grid_chimerax_2.png?raw=true\">\r\n    <img src=\"https://github.com/rdk/p2rank/blob/develop/documentation/img/visualization/pocket_grid_chimerax_2_small.png?raw=true\" height=\"230\" alt=\"ChimeraX visualization of pockets as volumes / grid points\">\r\n  </a>\r\n</p>\r\n",
    "discussion_url": "https://github.com/rdk/p2rank/discussions/84"
  },
