    "body": "Feature release that brings speed optimizations, ChimeraX visualizations, and improvements to rescoring.\r\n\r\nMain changes:\r\n\r\n* supported Java versions: 17 to 23 (Java 11 is no longer supported)\r\n* speed optimizations\r\n  * ~2x speedup on large datasets (due to faster model inference)\r\n  * ~2x speedup when processing a single file (due to faster model loading)\r\n* added [ChimeraX](https://github.com/RBVI/ChimeraX) visualizations (thanks to @JavierSanchez-Utges and @elainecmeng for help)\r\n  * new `-vis_renderers 'pymol,chimerax'` parameter to turn individual visualization renderers on/off \r\n* rescoring improvenemts\r\n  * `prank rescore` command now generates a `predictions.csv` file and can serve as a drop-in replacement for `prank predict` in most scenarios\r\n  * new `prank fpocket-rescore` command to automatically run [fpocket](https://github.com/Discngine/fpocket) and rescore its predictions\r\n  * new experimental rescoring model `prank rescore -c rescore_2024`\r\n\r\nThis version contains the same prediction models as version 2.4 .\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\">\r\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/rdk/p2rank/blob/develop/misc/img/p2rank_chimerax_visualization.png?raw=true\">\r\n    <img src=\"https://github.com/rdk/p2rank/blob/develop/misc/img/p2rank_chimerax_visualization_small.png?raw=true\" width=\"400\" alt=\"ChimeraX visualization\">\r\n  </a>\r\n</p>",
